<div id="show-taxi" class="item--content">
  <h3>Taxis</h3>
      <ul class="no-list">
        <li><p>NYC taxis can be hailed throughout Manhattan by holding your arm in the air on the street corner. Avaiablle taxis have the center light atop their roof on.  Lights off mean the taxi is occupied.  Taxis also have an ‘off duty’ light atop the car.</p></li>
      
        <li><p>The meter is required to be engaged or "hired" when a taxicab is occupied by anyone in addition to the driver. The Standard City Rate is $2.50 upon entry and $0.50 for each additional unit. The unit fare is:</p></li>
      
        <li><p>1/5 of a mile, when the taxicab is traveling at 6 miles an hour or more; or 60 seconds when not in motion or traveling at less than 6 miles per hour.  Night surcharge of $.50 after 8:00 PM &amp; before 6:00 AM Peak hour Weekday Surcharge of $1.00 Monday - Friday after 4:00 PM & before 8:00 PM.  New York State Tax Surcharge of $.50 per ride. </p></li>
    <li>
      <h3>Taxi Apps</h3>
        <li><p><a href="https://www.goarro.com/" target="_blank">ARRO</a>: once you download the application and create a profile, you will be able to hail a cab as well as pay for the cab via this application.  Additionally, if you hail a taxi off the street, once in the cab you will see a 7 digit code on the TV screen to insert into the app to pay and get an email receipt.</p></li>
      </ul>
</div>